{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, the model tends to conflate semantically related actions across datasets (e.g., IDLE vs.",
    "STILL, RETRACTION vs.",
    "PULL), where functionally similar gestures are expressed under different naming conventions (see Fig. 5(c)).",
    "We argue that this imbalance leads to reduced numerical accuracy, even when the predicted actions remain contextually valid.",
    "Generalization Ability."
  ]
}